other_tests.findings: Induced a marked increase in LH (baseline: 0.9 IU/liter; peak: 19.3 IU/liter) and FSH (baseline: 3.8 IU/liter; peak: 20.9 IU/liter).
Demonstrated no increase in LH, FSH, or estradiol levels.
Failed to normalize LH/FSH ratio; with doses ranging from 75 to 500 ng/kg, resulted in increased follicle size but inadequate estradiol rise and absence of ovulation.
other_tests.changes_over_time: At doses of 100 ng/kg, 150 ng/kg, and 250 ng/kg, partial follicular development occurred, but estradiol remained low and failed to induce ovulation.
